  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Because I knew that thou art obstinate,.... Or \"hard\" (a), hard hearted, an obdurate and rebellious people, contradicting and gainsaying: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and thy neck is as an iron sinew; stiffnecked, inflexible, not compliant with the will of God, and his commands; unwilling to admit his yoke, and bear it: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and thy brow brass; impudent, not ashamed of sin, nor blushing at it, refusing to receive correction for it, having a whore's forehead. This the Lord knew and foreknew, and therefore declared before hand what would come to pass unto them; who otherwise would have had the assurance to have ascribed them to themselves, or their idols, and not to him. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(a)   \"quod durus tu es\", Pagninus, Montanus; \"te durum esse\", Junius & Tremellius, Piscator, Vitringa. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(a)   \"quod durus tu es\", Pagninus, Montanus; \"te durum esse\", Junius & Tremellius, Piscator, Vitringa. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
