        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "After this summons, and description of those who are summoned, the address of Jehovah begins. \"The first I have long ago proclaimed, and it has gone forth out of my mouth, and I caused it to be heard. I carried it out suddenly, and it came to pass. Because I knew that thou art hard, and thy neck an iron clasp, and thy brow of brass; I proclaimed it to thee long ago; before it came to pass, I caused thee to hear it, that thou mightest not say, My idol has done it, and my graven image and molten image commanded it.\" The word הראשׁנות in itself signifies simply priora; and then, according to the context, it signifies prius facta (",
        "children": []
